videoSnippet.title: What's The Idea Here? Undeveloped Pieces Allow for Some Dirty Tactics!
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Here is a game from Round 5 Of Križevci Chess Club Championship I played today. Some interesting variation happened in the game :) Last year I won first place, winning all games and drawing one. So far I'm 5/5, 2 more games to go.
Time control was 90min + 30 sec increment per move.
I missed some better continuations, but, that's why we analyze games :)

Marijan Garac vs Antonio Radić
Križevci Chess Club Championship 2018., Križevci, Croatia, rd 5, Feb-11
King's Pawn Opening: Owen's Defense (B00)

1. e4 b6 2. d4 Bb7 3. Bd3 Nf6 4. Qe2 e6 5. Nf3 d5 6. exd5 Nxd5 7. c3 Nd7 8. O-O Bd6 9. a3 O-O 10. Be3 e5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13. Bxh7+ Kxh7 14. Qh5+ Kg8 15. Qxe5 Re8 16. Qg3 Re6 17. Bg5 Qd7 18. Qh3 Qb5 19. b4 Qxf1+ 20. Kxf1 Ba6+
